TopicTitle: Help! Curious Logspam: "[PartSet]: Failed to add Resource..."

Articles.Content:
My latest 1.6.1 KSP install is running really smoothly, so I'm surprised that all of the sudden I'm getting a ton of logspam and KSP is CTD'ing, so I'm trying to understand what I'm seeing in the log.

Can anyone identify what this error is coming from? Is this mod-related or something with Unity?

Here's a portion of the spam which (I assume?) is contributing to my CTD problem: 

[LOG 20:47:57.396] [PartSet]: Failed to add Resource 374119730 to Simulation PartSet:13702 as corresponding Part FL-TX1800 Fuel Tank-290656617 SimulationResource was not found.
[LOG 20:47:57.396] [PartSet]: Failed to add Resource 374119730 to Simulation PartSet:13702 as corresponding Part FL-TX1800 Fuel Tank-290656617 SimulationResource was not found.

[LOG 20:47:57.396] [PartSet]: Failed to add Resource 374119730 to Simulation PartSet:13601 as corresponding Part FL-TX1800 Fuel Tank-290656617 SimulationResource was not found.

Here's the full log file for reference: KSP Log 032719 T2148.log

Background:

  • I'm getting this now when I'm playing a Sandbox game, which it doesn't seem to happen in my Career game
  • The CTDs are happening since I've been building a large spacecraft that has ~ 500 parts, plus adding a bunch more (attached station)
  • So far this is only in the SPH, since it's just been since I'm building this craft. I haven't had any problems in Map/Flight or KSC/Menu.
  • My system specs: i5 6600, GTX 1060, 16GB RAM, Win10

Also, here are the mods I'm running:

Hi, yeah, I have the same issue in the current version of the game. In my case, I think the error is connected to me wanting to put LH2 into fuel tanks for Cryogenic Engines, but despite the editor showing it to be there, when I want to launch my rocket, it's filled with normal LF. So, I think this problem is related to B9PartSwitch or the Community Resource Pack, since those are the only addons that deal with resources and that we all have in common here.

EDIT: I found a solution, at least for my version of the issue: I had B9PartSwitch AND SimpleFuelSwitch installed and apparently they conflict? Getting rid of the FuelSwitch plugin solved the issue for me.

@MaxwellsDemon that's an issue with ContractConfigurator which is a dependency of just about all contract packs and is somewhat unmaintained right now.

See the post below by phoenix2004uk for an mm patch then keep reading for methods to fix it in an existing save. 

 

As for the PartSet bug, I get it, too. Don't believe it contributes to any crashes (ksp doesn't usually log anything useful in diagnosing a crash, therefore logspam can be annoying but might not be your most serious issue). Most likely memory access crashes. Uninstalling scatterer improved the frequency of these for me (makes sense as it is out of date and players have been reporting the same experience for years). 

Other mods mentioned that can cause issues:

AmpYear and [X] Science! - both allocate a ton of memory every frame, AmpYear scales with part count, x science with experiments and situations. 

Kopernicus (at least the 1.7.3 version) has problems with scatter, breaking ground features, and bodies with no oceans. There are workarounds available in the support forum for some of those issues.
